=TEX
{} and
=INLINEFT
e‰2
=TEX
{} has type 
=INLINEFT
Ó‰2
=TEX
{}  then
=INLINEFT
(e‰1, e‰2)
=TEX
{} has type
=INLINEFT
Ó‰1 * Ó‰2
=TEX
.  A tuple
=INLINEFT
(e‰1, ..., e‰n)
=TEX
{} is  NOT  equivalent to
=INLINEFT
(e‰1, (e‰2, ..., e‰n))
=TEX
