=TEX
{} (head of a list), which is applicable to lists of any type:

\begin{session}
=SML
      hd;
=GFT
      val it = fn : 'a list -> 'a   
=TEX
\end{session}

This example also shows that, in the system's response, the value of a function is not displayed in full, but only symbolized by the letters
=INLINEFT
